  "prompt": "Does Cyanogen 13.1 on Moto G3 support VOLTE? If yes, how can I turn on?",
  "response": "CyanogenMod 13.1, based on Android 6.0 (Marshmallow), does not natively support VoLTE (Voice over LTE) functionality on devices like the Moto G3. VoLTE capabilities are typically dependent on both the hardware of the device and the software modifications implemented by the ROM.\n\nHowever, some custom ROMs may include patches or functionalities that allow VoLTE, but this is not guaranteed. If your version of CyanogenMod or any other custom ROM you may be using doesn\u2019t explicitly mention VoLTE support, it\u2019s likely that it won\u2019t work.\n\nHere are steps to check for and enable VoLTE if your ROM supports it:\n\n1. **Check for VoLTE Support**:\n   - Go to **Settings** > **About phone** > **Build number**. Tap it several times to enable Developer Options if not already enabled.\n   - Return to **Settings**, then go to **Developer options** and look for any settings related to VoLTE or IMS.\n\n2. **Enable VoLTE**:\n   - Go to **Settings** > **Network & internet** > **Mobile network**.\n   - Look for an option named **Advanced** or **Enhanced 4G LTE Mode**. If you see it, enable it.\n\n3. **Check Carrier Compatibility**:\n   - Ensure that your mobile carrier supports VoLTE on your device. Some carriers may have specific requirements or need you to enable it from their side.\n\n4. **APN Settings**:\n   - You may need to modify your APN settings to support VoLTE. Check your carrier\u2019s website or support for the correct APN settings.\n\n5. **Reboot** your device after changing any settings.\n\nIf none of the above options are available, your best alternative would be to look for a different custom ROM that explicitly supports VoLTE for the Moto G3, or consider returning to the stock ROM if VoLTE is important for your needs.",
